  "text": "In analysis of the gene region for the SCAl syndrome on chromosome 6p22-p23 (9, lo), the results of multipoint linkage analyses with markers D6S309, D6S259, D6S285, and TNFB excluded a contiguous area of more than 20 cM extending on both sides of the SCAl locus as a site for the IOSCA gene. Analogously, linkage analyses of markers D12S82, D12S78, D12S86, and D12S76 excluded a continuous area of nearly 50 cM on distal 12q as the IOSCA locus, the exclusion flanking the SCA2 locus on 12q23-q24.1 (1 1). Finally, multipoint linkage analysis of markers D14S80, D14S75, D14S269, D14S66, D14S63, D14S43, and D14S74 demonstrated that the IOSCA gene is not located on the region of 70 cM covered by these markers and thus does not represent the same allelic locus as the FSP syndrome type assigned to this chromosomal region [CITATION_1] (Fig. 3) .",
